                    <b>Temperature Fluctuations</b>
                    <p>
                      Temperature fluctuations are a critical issue for wine cellars, as consistent temperatures are vital for preserving the quality and longevity of wine. Ideally, wine should be stored at a stable temperature between 55°F and 58°F. Fluctuations can cause wine to expand and contract, potentially damaging the cork and allowing air to seep into the bottle, leading to oxidation. Common causes of temperature instability include malfunctioning cooling units, poor insulation, and inadequate sealing of the cellar space. Addressing this issue may involve repairing or replacing cooling systems, improving insulation, and ensuring that doors and windows are properly sealed. Costs can range from <b>$300</b> for minor adjustments to over <b>$2,000</b> for comprehensive system overhauls.
                    </p>
                  </li>

